sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159110
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Thermonuclease with N-terminal SV40 NLS and flexible linker with TEV site in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes a micrococcal nuclease (Thermonuclease) with N-terminal SV40 Nuclear Localization Signal (SV40 NLS) and a flexible linker with a TEV cleavage site. Thermonuclease degrades ssDNA/dsDNA/ssRNA/dsRNA. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix for further protein fusions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159310
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 34 AA flexible linker with C-terminal TEV cleavage site (GGGGS)x5-TEV-site-linker) in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes a 34 amino acids long flexible linker ((GlyGlyGlyGlySer)x5) with a C-terminal cleavage site for the TEV Protease. For further protein fusions this part is flanked by RFC[25} pre- and suffix.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Mature Nuclease NucA from Staphylococcus aureus (Thermonuclease) in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Thermonuclease is a endo-exonuclease from ''Staphylococcus aureus'' that degrades dsDNA, ssDNA, dsRNA and ssRNA.
